\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\b\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Game Sense vs. Mechanical Skill}{\s28\f0\fs24\b\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\fi720\s28\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Every competitive FPS must strike a balance between promoting game sense and mechanical skill. Game sense is the combination of }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}knowledge}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0} and }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}experience}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0} that creates optimal play by minimizing mistakes, while mechanical skill is the raw aim and movement that come from }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}practice}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}. Any successful competitive FPS player must have both strong game sense and strong mechanical skill, but different games emphasize one over the other.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}}